segment.source: The following information can help you diagnose what causes assessments to fail.
segment.target: The following information can help you diagnose what causes assessments to fail.

segment.source: Assessment Didn't Produce Any Results
segment.target: Assessment Didn't Produce Any Results

segment.source: If you receive an error message and the assessment didn't produce any results, use this method to view the log files:
segment.target: If you receive an error message and the assessment didn't produce any results, use this method to view the log files:

segment.source: In the Windows Assessment Console, on the View Results page, choose Total errors, and then expand the error that appears in the details pane on the right.
segment.target: In the Windows Assessment Console, on the View Results page, choose Total errors, and then expand the error that appears in the details pane on the right.

segment.source: Choose the link under Further analysis to open the folder where the log files are stored.
segment.target: Choose the link under Further analysis to open the folder where the log files are stored.

segment.source: The folder contains AxeLog.etl trace files that you can open in Windows Performance Analyzer (WPA).
segment.target: The folder contains AxeLog.etl trace files that you can open in Windows Performance Analyzer (WPA).

segment.source: The folder also contains ErrorWarnings.xml files and AXELog.txt files.
segment.target: The folder also contains ErrorWarnings.xml files and AXELog.txt files.

segment.source: The text file is a compilation of all of the Event Trace Log (ETL) files that are produced after the job finishes.
segment.target: The text file is a compilation of all of the Event Trace Log (ETL) files that are produced after the job finishes.

segment.source: The Assessment fails to complete
segment.target: The Assessment fails to complete

segment.source: The job completes, but the assessment doesn't run.
segment.target: The job completes, but the assessment doesn't run.

segment.source: One of the following error codes might be reported by the assessment:
segment.target: One of the following error codes might be reported by the assessment:

segment.source: This error occurs when maintenance tasks have been registered on the PC but have not completed before the assessment run.
segment.target: This error occurs when maintenance tasks have been registered on the PC but have not completed before the assessment run.

segment.source: This prevents the assessment from running, as maintenance tasks often impact assessment metrics.
segment.target: This prevents the assessment from running, as maintenance tasks often impact assessment metrics.

segment.source: To resolve this issue, do one of the following:
segment.target: To resolve this issue, do one of the following:

segment.source: Ensure that the computer is connected to a network and is running on AC power.
segment.target: Ensure that the computer is connected to a network and is running on AC power.

segment.source: Manually initiate pending maintenance tasks with the following command from an elevated prompt:
segment.target: Manually initiate pending maintenance tasks with the following command from an elevated prompt:

segment.source: rundll32.exe advapi32.dll,ProcessIdleTasks
segment.target: rundll32.exe advapi32.dll,ProcessIdleTasks

segment.source: Disable regular and idle maintenance tasks, and stop all maintenance tasks before running the assessment
segment.target: Disable regular and idle maintenance tasks, and stop all maintenance tasks before running the assessment
